<SLUG> BC-BBA-ANGELNOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ANGELS INFIELDERS VIE FOR POSITIONS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JOE HAAKENSON  
 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   TEMPE, Ariz. _ With Cactus League games set to begin Friday, one
of manager Angels manager Mike Scioscia's tasks this spring is to
determine who will be on his bench.
</P>
<P>
   He has seven players vying for the starting job at second base,
leaving the others to battle for a utility infielder role.
</P>
<P>
   Scott Spiezio is the only one with a major-league contract and
started 59 games last season for Oakland. Justin Baughman, having
recovered from a broken leg, could give the club some speed, but he
hasn't played since suffering the injury in a Mexican Winter League
game in November of 1998.
</P>
<P>
   The others in the hunt are Jason Bates, Pat Kelly, Benji Gil,
Carlos Garcia and Trent Durrington.
</P>
<P>
   ``The key for the guy making our team as a utility player is
being able to play shortstop,'' Scioscia said. ``If you can play
shortstop, you can play second and hold your own at third. Whoever
can play short will be huge in who makes the team.''
</P>
<P>
   Baughman can play shortstop, but if he doesn't make the team as
the starter at second, he'll likely go to the minors so he can play
every day to make up for the time he lost to the injury. Garcia,
Bates and Gil have recent experience at shortstop. Spiezio, Kelly
and Durrington do not play there.
</P>
<P>
   Beating ASU: Garret Anderson had two hits and starting pitcher
Scott Schoeneweis struck out four in two innings as the Angels beat
Arizona State 7-3 at Tempe Diablo Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   Darin Erstad and Gary DiSarcina had one hit each and Bengie
Molina had a hit and two RBI as most of the Angels regulars were
finished by the third inning. Reliever Greg Keagle, who pitched in
the Tigers organization last season, pitched 2 scoreless innings.
</P>
<P>
   Schoeneweis appeared in 31 games last season with the Angels -
all as a reliever - but Scioscia said he should be included in the
battle for starting spots along with Ramon Ortiz, Jarrod Washburn
and Brian Cooper.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's in the mix, no doubt about it,'' Scioscia said. ``He
obviously has the arm to pitch in the major leagues. And I think
with his maturity and makeup as a pitcher he's going to be good.''
</P>
<P>
   Short hops: Jim Edmonds was excused from Wednesday's workout and
game because of personal reasons involving his children. He's
expected back today.... Dennis Wyrick, a freshman from Bishop Amat
High, started at shortstop for ASU. Wednesday night.... The Angels
signed pitcher Mike Fyhrie and outfielder Jeff DaVanon to contracts
for the 2000 season.... Pitching matchups for this weekend's Cactus
League games: Friday - Jarrod Washburn vs. Jamie Moyer (Mariners);
Saturday - Ken Hill vs. Gil Heredia (A's); Sunday - Kent Mercker
vs. Kevin Appier (A's).
</P>
</TEXT>
