<P>
   NY-BUSH-PATAKI (New York) _ With George W. Bush's convincing
victories in North Dakota, Washington and Virginia on Tuesday, the
governor of Texas turns to New York, hoping that the vote in that
state next Tuesday will help him finally nail down a nomination.
Bush, though, is not the only governor with a lot riding on next
Tuesday's vote, and that becomes abundantly clear as Gov. George
Pataki's apparatus tries to assure that Pataki does not join the
list of Republican governors who have failed Bush during his
difficult political year. By Adam Nagourney and Richard Perez-Pena.
