<P>
   OIL-MARKETPLACE (Undated) _ Crude oil prices surge on world oil
markets despite statements from officials of Saudi Arabia,
Venezuela and Mexico that they are prepared to increase production.
Story will also look at the dollar's recent surge against the yen
and the euro. By Jonathan Fuerbringer.
</P>
<P>
   ABC-CABLE _ ABC is threatening to pull its signal off the Time
Warner cable system in Houston, leaving 650,000 homes without the
network's programming. The move speaks volumes about the changing
economics of the television business, in particular the growth of
the satellite industry, which is giving new leverage to the
networks. And it also reflects the increasing clout of the game
show ``Who Wants to Be a Millionaire.'' Disney, ABC's parent, is
demanding that Time Warner shift the Disney Cable Channel from a
pay, or premium, service to a basic service. Time Warner says this
is too costly and will force a rise in cable rates. By Bill Carter.
</P>
<P>
   WATER-AD-COLUMN (Undated) With bottled water _ no color, no
flavor, no image to speak of _ turning out to be one of its star
performers, growing far faster than colas and other carbonated soft
drinks, PepsiCo plans to spend millions of dollars to promote its
Aquafina brand in the coming year. By Constance L. Hays
</P>
