   &UR; AS FLOODWATERS ROSE, THE WORLD JUST WATCHED. WHY? &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Finally, a major if still barely coordinated relief effort is
under way for Mozambique. But the flurry of action has not been
nearly enough to mollify the anger of international aid agencies at
what they condemn as yet another ``pathetic'' failure of the rich
and self-centered West to respond with sufficient speed to a crisis
in a Third World country. ``If this had happened in the West, the
response would have been entirely different,'' said an angry relief
worker. &QL;
