<P>
   Admittedly, the electoral fat lady has not yet sung. But with a
string of victories for George W. Bush in the GOP primaries on
Tuesday that left John McCain, his challenger, sprawled on the
ropes, it looks increasingly as though the race will ultimately
come down _ predictably _ to Bush and Al Gore. It may not be
exciting, but countries have faced worse problems than that. &QL;
</P>
