<P>
   &UR; DO-OR-DIE: MCCAIN MUST WIN CALIFORNIA, NEW YORK TO STAY ALIVE &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The race for the Republican nomination for president now enters
its most intensive phase. The electoral calender is closing in on
John McCain. George W. Bush's sheer power of organization and
establishment support should now start to count. Unless McCain wins
California and New York next week, his campaign is all but dead. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Political, Commentary Editors) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   By Andrew Marshall, The Independent of London &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Moved Wed., March 1) &QL;
</P>
