   FASHION
</P>
<P>
   KIDS-CASUALCLOTHES _ Remember when children's dresser drawers
were neatly divided between school clothes and play clothes? Dick
and Jane would come home from a hard day of study, but before they
could hit the swing set, Mom gently reminded them to change into
short pants and sneakers. Doesn't happen much anymore, with
students already sporting playground-ready attire at school.
Clothes do affect behavior, and Americans are unmatched for casual
dress and rudeness. But the standards are changing. (Sturrock, Palm
Beach Post). WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
