<P>
   WITH: N.Y. TIMES BEST SELLERS LIST
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-NOTES _ Georgia author Henry Joseph has not had much luck
with U.S. publishers, but the French love him. Editions Gallimard,
the company that published Camus, has bought world rights to six of
Joseph's novels. Meanwhile, although his one English-language book,
``Bloodwork,'' is out of print, movie rights have been sold to the
producer of ``Hoosiers.'' (O'Briant, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
21.
