<P>
   GARCIA-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Rather than engage in prophecy,
the experienced political watcher often will speak in hypothetical.
Since Gov. George W. Bush's defeat in New Hampshire, some folks
around here are using poker slang in assessing his situation.
(Arnold Garcia is editorial page editor of the Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   MCNEELY-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ In recent days, the Bush
campaign's recurrent claim that McCain's ``Straight Talk Express''
is guilty of recurrent moving violations has been accompanied by
increasingly critical press scrutiny. (McNeely, Austin
American-Statesman) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Rather than spend his free time
campaigning for himself, in recent weeks Texas school board member
Bob Offutt spent time campaigning against Bush. The Steve Forbes
campaign flew Offutt and former board member Donna Ballard to New
Hampshire and Iowa to tell Republicans how wrong Bush is about
education. (John Young is opinion page editor of the Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVED
</P>
