other major powers who are so anxious to resume trade with Baghdad.
Indeed, America's greatest obstacles are the efforts by France,
Russia and other defenders to readmit Iraq into the community of
nations without requiring it to adhere to international norms.
</P>
<P>
   Unfortunately, standing alone may be self-defeating, despite its
moral attractiveness. But the perfect should not become the enemy
