<SLUG> BC-BANANA-WAL-MART-HNS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;     BANANA REPUBLIC CHIEF TO HEAD WAL-MART'S ON-LINE AFFILIATE 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 &HT;     By VICTORIA COLLIVER  
 &HT;     c.2000 San Francisco Examiner  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO _ The chief executive of Banana Republic, which is
owned by San Francisco-based Gap Inc., is leaving the specialty
retailer to become the head of Wal-Mart's on-line division.
</P>
<P>
   Jeanne Jackson, 48, has headed Banana Republic since 1996 while
also overseeing the on-line operations for the Gap brands for the
past two years.
</P>
<P>
   ``Wal-Mart has become such an incredible leader. It's one of the
most admired companies in the world,'' said Jackson, speaking
Wednesday about her opportunity to join what is considered to be
the world's largest retailer.
</P>
<P>
   The Web site for Bentonville, Ark.-based Wal-Mart Stores Inc.
has gone through a dramatic restructuring this year.
</P>
<P>
   On Jan. 6, the company announced the creation of a separate
company, Wal-Mart.com. Wal-Mart still holds the majority interest
in the on-line company. On Jan. 1, Wal-Mart also launched a
redesigned site with additional features.
</P>
<P>
   ``We'll evolve from the site that exists. We'll hopefully keep
what's good, improve what needs improving, add features that don't
yet exist,'' Jackson said.
</P>
<P>
   Jackson's 22-year career in retail includes positions with
Federated Department Stores Inc., Saks Fifth Avenue, Walt Disney
Company and Victoria's Secret.
</P>
<P>
   She has been named by Fortune magazine as one of the ``50 Most
Powerful Women'' in U.S. business each of the past two years.
</P>
<P>
   Millard ``Mickey'' Drexler, the chief executive of Gap Inc.,
said in a statement that Jackson has left behind an exceptionally
strong management team at Banana Republic.
</P>
<P>
   ``In her five years here, Jeanne has helped build Banana
Republic into a leading apparel brand, and in the past year and a
half she's helped to expand our business on line,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Jackson's starting date is yet to be determined, but she expects
to begin in April. Wal-Mart.com is temporarily being based in Palo
Alto.
</P>
<P>
   Gap on Wednesday announced it had formed an office of the
president to run the Banana Republic business until a permanent
chief executive is named. The office will be run by three Banana
Republic executives: Jerome Jessup, Gary Muto and Amy Schoening.
</P>
<P>
   Ron Beegle, who has been leading the day-to-day operations at
Gap's direct-to-consumer business, was named head of the on-line
business.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
