r l BC-DRJOY-COLUMN-ADV10-NY     03-02 0739
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-DRJOY-COLUMN-ADV10-NYTSF </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
$ADV10 
 FOR USE FRIDAY, MARCH 10, OR ANYTIME THEREAFTER
</HEADLINE>
  ATTENTION EDITORS: The following material from The New York Times
Syndicate is for use by DRJOY-COLUMN clients. Nonsubscribers can
use this article only by special arrangement. For purchase
information, call (888)-269-8796. 
 I LOVE A MAN MY FAMILY WILL NOT ACCEPT  
 By DR. JOY BROWNE 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features)  
<TEXT>
<P>
   DEAR DR. JOY: I'm 17 years old and I've had a few boyfriends.
The guy I'm interested in now is 26 years old and lives in Texas.
He's been my pen pal for more than a year. We've discovered that we
love each other.
</P>
<P>
   This summer, I'm planning on meeting him. Recently he's brought
up the subject of sex. When I go down there, would it be wrong if I
did have sex with him?
</P>
<P>
   My grandmother, I'm sure, would not approve. She says that we
should be friends for two years. I'm sure that back in her day,
young people had sex when they were in love, even though she denies
it. _ W.
</P>
<P>
   DR. JOY: I'm not sure of your question. Are you expecting me to
give you permission to have sex with someone you've never met? If
so, you may have come to the wrong psychologist. Regardless, let me
talk you through your situation.
</P>
<P>
   I think it's wonderful that you have a pen pal, and you're
exploring your emotions at arm's length. I would probably be as
excited as you are about meeting him for the first time, but slow
down a bit!
</P>
<P>
   When you meet your pen pal, you should not stay with him. A
chaperoned visit _ perhaps with a friend _ may make you feel a
little safer. The fact is, you don't know this guy. You know the
fantasy of who you hope is, and he knows what his fantasy is of
you. The real people have yet to meet.
</P>
<P>
   My problem with the two of you having sex is not only the age
difference _ in certain states you are legally considered a minor
and he could be accused of statutory rape _ or that you don't
really know him. The fact is _ even if you are madly in love with
him _ after the visit, you will return to finish high school and
he'll go back to Texas.
</P>
<P>
   The safest way for the two of you to maintain a long distance
relationship is without sex. It's fine to fantasize, but for right
now I suggest that you get to know each other better _ and not in
the biblical sense. No sex!
</P>
<P>
   The first time you have sex with someone should be very special
and you don't want it to be with a stranger. You want to feel that
you know this person.
</P>
<P>
   I know that you feel you do know him, but take your time. I
promise that you when you do have sex for the first time, whether
it's with this man or not, you want to feel that the person will be
there for you, not only that night, but the next morning and,
hopefully, for a long while to come.
</P>
<P>
   DEAR DR. JOY: In June of this year, I found out that my husband
of two years was married to another women in Ohio. When he found
out that I knew, he put a gun to my head and threatened to kill me.
</P>
<P>
   I escaped from this Gulf War veteran and am losing mostly
everything in the divorce due to the fact that nothing was in my
name. I have lost my husband and my sense of security. I have
gotten no help from lawyers. Do you have any advice to help me pull
my life back together? _ J.
</P>
<P>
   DR. JOY: The good news is that you have gotten out of that
situation. You need to stay away from men for a while. My guess is
that you don't trust your judgment anymore.
</P>
<P>
   I don't know how long you knew this charm school graduate before
you married him. I suspect not very long. For right now, you need
to focus on being self-sufficient. Understand that all of us have
been fools for love at one time or another, but it is important not
to continue the pattern.
</P>
<P>
   Find a job if you don't have one. Become emotionally and
financially self-sufficient and give yourself some time.
</P>
<P>
   Now is a great time for you to take a course or do some
volunteer activities. You'll feel smarter and a lot more useful.
</P>
<P>
   -----
</P>
