years, from the confederate flag that flies over the South Carolina
statehouse to the names on school buildings of historic figures who
owned slaves. Now the Declaration of Independence is under siege on
the grounds that its 1776 statement that ``all men are created
equal'' didn't include blacks (or women) at the time. But this
protest misses the forest for the trees. By MARIANNE MEANS.
