tank where they would normally stay all day. 220 words. By Joanna
Marchant. Slugged: BC-FISH-FOLLOW-LEADER-(NEW-SCIENTIST)-NYTSF)
</P>
<P>
   EARLY HUMANS BUILT HUTS 500,000 YEARS AGO &LR;  _ It's possible that
half a million years ago our ancestors, Homo erectus, were building
huts. Japanese archaeologists have found what is believed to be the
remains of the world's oldest artificial structure on a hillside
north of Tokyo. 600 words. By Peter Hadtfield. Slugged:
BC-ANCIENT-REAL-ESTATE-(NEW-SCIENTIST)-NYTSF) &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL;
