<P>
   UNDATED _ If there's one sport that vid-game companies still
scratch their heads over on how to make it cool for kids _ much
less knuckleheaded adults like me _ it's golf. It takes hours to
figure out most golf games, even the supposedly kid-friendly ones.
Sorry, but I just don't have the patience. I like to win every once
in a while. That was what was so great about Hot Shots Golf,
PlayStation's very cool, very oblivious-user-friendly golf title
from last year. The sequel, Hot Shots Golf 2 (Sony for PlayStation,
$40), is even better. By MALCOLM MAYHEW. Story has moved in ``e''
entertainment category. &QL; 
