<P>
   UNDATED _ Like a dog biting your pants leg, James Champy just
won't let go. First, the management consultant invents
re-engineering with his book ``Reengineering the Corporation.'' He
tells us to go through every process, every procedure, every
traditional way-it's-always-been-done system and tweak it until it
runs faster, smoother and more profitably. His book hits bestseller
status, coins a buzzword and, with his consulting work, starts a
movement in business. By TERESA MCUSIC. Story has moved in ``f''
financial category. &QL; 
