<HEADLINE>
SHANDLING'S `PLANET' REVOLVES AROUND CRUDE HUMOR 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By WILLIAM ARNOLD  
 c.2000 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Comedian Garry Shandling is reportedly the best friend of
Hollywood power-couple Warren Beatty and Annette Bening, which
explains what A-level star Bening is doing in Shandling's D-level
wannabe star vehicle, ``What Planet Are You From?''
</P>
<P>
   But what the heck is Mike Nichols' name doing in the producer
and director's credits of this ghastly unfunny misfire? Not once in
his distinguished career _ not even in his 1975 career nadir, ``The
Fortune'' _ has he made such a witless, low-humor comedy.
</P>
<P>
   The film is a sci-fi sex farce in the tradition of ``Earth Girls
Are Easy'' and ``Invasion of the Girl Snatchers.'' Shandling plays
an agent from a superior, all-male, alien planet sent to Earth to
impregnate an Earth girl: the beginning of the gradual subversion
of our culture from within.
</P>
<P>
   Heavily trained back on his planet and disguised as a banker
from Seattle, he thinks his task will be a snap, but his efforts at
quick seduction are constantly being frustrated by the clash of
sexual cultures, and by a bionic penis, which emits an irritating
humming noise every time he's aroused.
</P>
<P>
   As the Earth girl he finally woos, marries and impregnates,
co-star Bening is so much better than anything else in the film
that she throws it strangely off-balance. This woman is a true
star, and obviously capable of being radiant and endearing in even
the most unlikely company and surroundings.
</P>
<P>
   And Shandling (TV's ``The Larry Sanders Show'') is not exactly
terrible in his first big-screen star vehicle: To a certain extent,
he carries the movie well on his shoulders. If his jokes were even
a little bit funnier and slightly more original, he might have
scraped by and established a career in this (for him) new medium.
</P>
<P>
   But the movie falls disastrously flat. Whole comedy subplots
involving John Goodman as a government airlines investigator on the
alien's trail, Ben Kinsley as the despotic leader of the alien
planet, and Greg Kinnear as Shandling's slimy co-worker in a
Phoenix bank fail to raise even a polite chuckle.
</P>
<P>
   Worse, the script fails to make anything amusing or satirically
clever out of its rich sexual culture-clash potential, and opts
instead for crude sexist humor, endless penis jokes and even
urinating baby gags. Could this be the same Mike Nichols who made
``The Graduate'' and ``Carnal Knowledge'' and ``Primary Colors?''
</P>
<P>
   What Planet Are You From? Directed by Mike Nichols. Screenplay
by Garry Shandling, Michael Leeson, Ed Solomon, Peter Tolan. Cast:
Garry Shandling, Annette Bening, John Goodman, Ben Kingsley.
Columbia. 100 minutes. Rated R for language and sex jokes.
</P>
<P>
   Grade: D
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-02-00 1752EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
