   FOREST-ROADS (Undated) _ In yet another sign of the greening of
the US Forest Service, Agriculture Secretary Dan Glickman proposes
a new policy for managing the 380,000 miles of logging roads in
America's 155 national forests. Plan emphasizes the repair and
maintenance of existing roads rather than construction of new ones.
By Robert Baile. 900 words.
