   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   DOUBLECLICK (Undated) _ Stung by protests from Internet privacy
advocates and a federal investigation, Internet advertising firm
DoubleClick Inc. halts its plan to use name and address data to
track the online activities of millions of consumers. By Hiawatha
Bray. 975 words.
</P>
<P>
   STAPLES-EARNS (Undated) _ Office supply giant Staples reports
great earnings, but its stock slides as an analyst warns that
staples.com losses will double. By Chris Reidy. 500 words.
</P>
<P>
   MATRITECH-CANCER (Undated) _ Shares of Matritech peak after the
company announces a blood test to detect the early stages of breast
cancer that will cost women $30. Clinical trial testing will start
later this year. By Ronald Rosenberg. 500 words.
</P>
<P>
   NFL-PATRIOTS (Boston) _ Connecticut officials say the NFL has
agreed to pay $2.4 million to settle all possible claims regarding
the Patriots' pullout from Hartford. By Meg Vaillancourt. 400
words. (f and s coding)
</P>
