<SLUG> BC-HMO-BAILOUT-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
HMO'S WOES EASING, REGULATORS TAKE HANDS-OFF APPROACH 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (a and f coding)   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By LIZ KOWALCZYK AND RICHARD A. KNOX  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BOSTON _ Rejecting all proposals from outside investors because
they came with too many strings attatched, state regulators said
they will rely on clever accounting and faith to keep Harvard
Pilgrim Health Care an independent nonprofit organization.
</P>
<P>
   Just two months after forcing the state's largest HMO into state
receivership and touching off a regional healthcare crisis,
