<HEADLINE>
WHAT WE CAN THANK PINOCHET FOR 
</HEADLINE>
   &HT;     (Because of its timeliness, we are re-releasing this article.
To publish it as a ``separate buy,'' please contact one of these
New York Times Syndicate sales representatives: 
 &HT;    (--U.S., Canada and the Pacific: CONNIE WHITE in Kansas City at
1-800-444-0267 or 816-822-8448, or fax her at 816-822-1444. 
 &HT;    (--Europe and Asia: KARL HORWITZ in Paris at 47-42-17-11; fax,
47-42-80-44 or 47-42-18-81; telex, 282-942. 
 &HT;    (--Latin America: ANA PENA in New York, 310-996-0075; fax,
310-996-0089. 
 &HT;    
 By JORGE G. CASTANEDA  
 c.2000 New York Times Special Features  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The arrest and detention of Augusto Pinochet served a purpose,
far beyond warming the hearts of the thousands of friends,
relatives and colleagues of his victims _ men and women who had
waited nearly a quarter of a century for justice and solace.
</P>
