<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
stories for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Thursday, March 2 and thereafter. For questions about stories,
please contact Michael McGarr at the Daily News, (818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   GOP-DEBATE (Los Angeles) _ Republican presidential candidates
debate in Los Angeles, only days before voters make their choice in
California's presidential primary. Will run late. By Rick Orlov.
(Will run in the ``a'' national and ``n'' state news files.)
</P>
<P>
   BELMONT-SHOWDOWN (Los Angeles) _ Key state and city politicians
are threatening to hold the Los Angeles Unified School District's
billion-dollar school construction program hostage unless the
school board reconsiders the fate of the abandoned Belmont Learning
Center. By Greg Gittrich. (Will run in the ``a'' national and ``n''
state news files.)
</P>
<P>
   GM-EVRECALL _ General Motors Corp. is recalling almost 1,000
electric vehicles from the 1997 model year because of a potential
fire hazard. The action includes the EV1 cars and Chevrolet S-10
pickups. Customers will get either a second-generation vehicle or a
gasoline powered vehicle. By Chris Sieroty. (Will run in the ``f''
financial news file.)
</P>
<P>
   HACKER-CHARGES (Los Angeles) _ Los Angeles police said that
federal and New Hampshire state prosecutors will be meeting today
to determine what charges to file against a teen-age hacker known
by the Internet screen name of ``Coolio,'' and suspected of being
linked to alleged vandalisms of Web sites operated by an Internet
security company and the anti-drug progrm Drug Abuse Resistance
Education. LAPD helped nab the 17-year-old last month and say he
has admitted to compromising more than 100 Internet sites.
</P>
