Guennol Collection: Cabinet of Wonders,'' an exhibit at the
Brooklyn Museum of Art, brings together for the first time more
than 40 gifts and works from the collection of Alastair Bradley and
Edith Park Martin. One item in the show, ``Leonine Goddess,'' is a
small sculpture thought to have been made in southwestern Iran
around 3,000 B.C. (Brooklyn Museum of Art/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT19) HARTFORD, Conn. -- March 2, 2000 -- DALI-EXHIBIT -- Some
60 Dali visions are on view in ``Salvador Dali's Optical
Illusions'' at the Wadsworth Atheneum in Hartford - said to be the
first Dali retrospective in this country in nearly 60 years and the
first devoted to his preoccupation with optics and visual
perception - as illustrated by his work, ``The Invisible Man.''
(The Wadsworth Atheneum/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
