<P>
   (NYT4) NEW YORK -- March 2, 2000 -- DINNER-THEATER-REVIEW-2 --
Lisa Emery, who plays Karen in the play ``Dinner With Friends,''
goes through her lines at the Variety Arts Theater. The play,
written by Donald Margulies and directed by Daniel Sullivan,
tackles thorny yet elemental topics like how the pragmatic minutiae
of a marriage: ``having kids, having to pay the mortgage, making
the deadline, marinating the snapper,'' in Gabe's words, can
eclipse the passion. (Norman Y. Lono/The New York Times)
</P>
