<P>
   (NYT1) NEW YORK -- March 2, 2000 -- OBIT-BODNE -- Mary Bodne in
1998, in her traditional seat in the lobby of her beloved Algonquin
Hotel where she greeted visitors for more then 50 years. Bodne, who
with her husband, Ben, fell in love with the hotel on their
honeymoon and later owned it for 41 years, died on Monday at Lenox
Hill Hospital in Manhattan. She was 93. (Fred R. Conrad/The New
York Times)
