<P>
   (NYT37) NEW YORK -- March 2, 2000 -- RICH&AMP;RICHER-1 -- Keeping up
with the Joneses used to mean buying a vacation home, a BMW,
perhaps, or first-class airplane tickets. But your own fleet of
planes? These days, though, even the superrich are finding that the
rules of the game are being rewritten with each stock market move.
Nelson Peltz made much of his $890 million in the '80s. ``You see
these young guys worth $3 billion to $4 billion, and you think to
yourself, 'What have I done wrong?' `` he wondered. (Ruth
Fremson/The New York Times)
</P>
