<P>
   (NYT31) INDIANAPOLIS -- March 2, 2000 -- IND-CHURCH-TAX-2 --
Pastor Gregory J. Dixon's Indianapolis Baptist Temple is on a
collision course with the IRS, one of a small but growing number of
New Testament churches that say they are not subject to federal tax
laws requiring employers to withhold income, Social Security and
Medicare taxes from workers. Dixon, 67, said the people who work at
the church are not employees and called the money they receive
``love gifts.'' (Mary Ann Carter/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT30) INDIANAPOLIS -- March 2, 2000 -- IND-CHURCH-TAX-1 --
Facing foreclosure in a tax dispute, the Indianapolis Baptist
Temple is trying to establish what it says are its rights by
forcing the IRS to act. On Saturday, the church plans a
demonstration in downtown Indianapolis to protest the ruling, and
says it expects as many as 2,000 members and supporters to march.
(Mary Ann Carter/The New York Times)
</P>
