exhibit works from the collection of Barney A. and Pam Ebsworth,
St. Louis collectors of American art. So it comes as no surprise
that this week the gallery has received three more works from
Ebsworth's collection: Charles Sheeler's ``Classic Landscape''
(1931), is one of them. (National Gallery of Art/The New York
Times)
